SIMPLE: dodger
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dodger
<hw>dodg"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
dodges or evades; one who plays fast and loose, or uses tricky
devices.</def> <rj><au>Smart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small handbill.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>See <er>Corndodger</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dodger</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dodger
<hw>Dodg"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>a member of the
professional baseball team called <membof>the Dodgers</membof>. At one
time the team was headquartered in Brooklyn, New York, when it was
called the Brooklyn Dodgers, but the franchise was transferred to Los
Angeles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dodgery</ent>⟦br⟧
